    "body": "This could probably be written as (which helps reduce the ugliness of the conditional compilation):\n\n``` rust\n#[cfg(unix)]\nfn lookup() -> Path {\n    if cfg!(target_os = \"android\") {\n        Path(\"/data/tmp\")\n    } else {\n        getenv_nonempty(\"TMPDIR\").unwrap_or_default(Path(\"/tmp\"))\n    }\n}\n```\n\n(The `cfg!` and `if` get evaluated at compile time, so there is no cost.)\n",
